subSubSection.paragraph:
Head (
Fig. 12
) with epistoma evenly convex; punctures subequal to diameter of ommatidium, covering dorsal surface, evenly spaced, separated by 2–3X puncture diameters; setae 2X longer than puncture diameter, present laterally, mostly absent medially. Labrum densely punctate, about 2X size of punctures on head and separated by less than puncture diameter. Antenna clavate (
Fig. 12
). Dorsal and ventral portions of eye roughly equal in size and shape. Gular horns short, not prominent.

Scutellum (
Fig. 12
) small, triangular, about 2X times wider than long. Elytron gradually broadening from base to widest point opposite posterior margin of metaventrite, then evenly arcuate to apices; striae impressed; strial punctures deep, distinct, never confluent; intervals slightly convex, punctation minute, evenly spaced. Stria 7 ending in lateral stria at humeral angle.
